# Cursor Rules

## Code Style
- Use Prettier formatting (tabs, no semicolons, single quotes)
- Be terse and direct
- Provide actual code, not high-level explanations

## Communication
- Be casual unless specified otherwise
- Treat user as expert
- Give answers immediately, explain after if needed
- No moral lectures or unnecessary disclaimers

## Code Changes
- Don't repeat entire code blocks unnecessarily
- Show only changed lines with context (before/after)
- Multiple code blocks are fine when needed

## Technical Preferences
- Use Next.js 16+ documentation: https://nextjs.org/docs
- TypeScript strict mode enabled
- Prefer type imports: `import {type X}`
- Minimal dependencies, clean code

## Project Context
- Next.js 16 App Router
- React 19
- TypeScript strict mode
- Tailwind CSS 4
- shadcn/ui components
- MDX for blog content

